  "In a way, what we're really trying to do is synchronize the current state of our CSS animations with our component. This, by definition, is the perfect use case for \u0000SKIP#259\u0000. To do this, inside of our effect, we'll use the browser's \u0000SKIP#260\u0000 API to get all the animations in our entire subtree.": "",
  "Next, we'll map over all of our \u0000SKIP#262\u0000, creating an array of promises that will each resolve once its animation has finished running.": "",
  "Then, once we have our array of promises, we can use \u0000SKIP#264\u0000 to wait for all of them to resolve –&nbsp;which they will once all the animations have finished running.": "",
